Comment: Well explained puzzle, simple enough for a clash

Goal section
* I guess "non-null" is not required, as the description "positive" is already sufficiently clear. Alternatively, please change it to "non-zero".
* "Exemple" should be spelled as "Example".
* The example doesn't really explain anything. Please either expand it or remove it.

Output section
* You may format "none" as a {{constant}} and remove the quotation marks.
* The condition for outputing "none" or nothing is NOT "result of the maximum value is equal to 0". The condition should be when there are no such pairs of [[a]] and [[b]] which satisfy the condition that a and b are both positive integers. Please amend the description in both lines.

Solution code
* This does not really affect the clash, but I notice that the condition in the middle (if r == "none") will never be triggered as r will never be a string.

Thanks.

I modified it with your requests which are pretty clear and justified!
